Join us for the first Socially Distanced 5K Trail Run Series at Badger Prairie Park. This event is not your average trail run! column9: Run into the Summer Solstice with this twilight 5K/10K event. See the sights of the quaint village of Kewaskum as you run or walk to beat the sunset on the eve of the longest day of the year. Both distances take off at 7 pm and finish with a celebration of the Solstice. Runners and walkers are invited to participate in the 5K distance. Participants in the 10K distance must be able to finish the course in under 90 minutes in order to guarantee that all participants finish before dark.

On March 20, 2018, our daughter, Olivia, was diagnosed with Type 1 Diabetes. As we learned how to cope with daily life, we received an amazing outpouring of support from our local JDRF chapter. Once we got our footing, we knew we wanted to give back and help with research. Olivia had been running races with us since she was born and had just begun actually running, not just riding in the stroller. This race was born out of that love of running and our strong desire to find a cure for Type 1. All of the proceeds from run.LIV.run will go towards finding a cure! Please, join us for a fun day on the trails! Food and beer will be provided after the race.

The Happy Birthday America 5k & 10k is a birthday celebration for America!  The 5k & 10k run/walk will have patriotic music, and more red, white, and blue than you can imagine!  The course starts and finishes in Estabrook Park.  It cruises downhill along Estabrook Parkway before turning north on the paved Oak Leaf Trail.  The 10k course completes the 5k loop, then continues along the Oak Leaf Trail, and will complete a 2nd loop. This is a fast and fun course you’re going to love!  After the race, everyone gets an America's Birthday cupcake!
